column32: Shortly after exposure to sunlight a person's skin around the chest and arms becomes red and itchy, and it can take up to a week for the symptoms to resolve. ... A more dramatic 'sun allergy' produces not just a rash, but large hives on sun-exposed skin - this super-rare condition is called solar urticaria.Jan 1, 2016Here's why some of us develop an allergy to sunlight - ScienceAlerthttps://www.sciencealert.com/here-s-what-happens-if-you-develop-an-allergy-to-sunlight
